sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K371031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This parts is a fusion protein between the N terminus 98 amino acid of pdu V protein and RFP protein(BBa_E1010). At two side is special DNA sequence that make this parts compatible to BBF RFC 53. The MPF and MSF is the abbreviation of meta-prefix and meta-suffix seperately. Because the N terminus is said to target pduV outside the pdu BMC, this part can be used to direct pduV98-GFP chimera onto BMC surface.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang Zhang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Citrobactor freudii, the strain was bought from NITE Biological Resource Center (NBRC). NBRC NO. is 12681. History:IFO 12681 <- Ajinomoto Co., Inc. (AJ 2619) <- ATCC 8090 <- C.H. Werkm

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K371024
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a short amino sequence used to link or fuse two protein domain together to make a large chimera protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang Zhang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is not long, so it can be easily get by direct annealing two oligonucleotides.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: different codons of Gly and Ser was choosed in order to ignore the mismatch between forward sequence and reverse sequence when they are annealing.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K371017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part encodes the 1-98 amino acid of the N terminus pdu V proterin. The N terminus of Pdu V is thought to target to the outside of bacterial microcompartment.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang Zhang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Citrobactor freudii, the strain was bought from NITE Biological Resource Center (NBRC). NBRC NO. is 12681. History:IFO 12681 <- Ajinomoto Co., Inc. (AJ 2619) <- ATCC 8090 <- C.H. Werkman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to isolate pduA from the Citrobactor freundii genome, following primers has been designed to make it a standard Biobrick.
